{"TopicId":140343,"ForumId":15,"TopicTitle":"Offset INTERNAL in cfg syntax?","CreatedByName":"Fwiffo","CreatedById":148084,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-23T08:17:59Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Fwiffo","CreatedById":148084,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-23T08:17:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCrewed modules have an INTERNAL section like the following:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode\u0022\u003E\nINTERNAL\n{\n\tname = landerCabinInternals\n}\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs it possible to offset the entire internal space? \u00A0Failing that, can anyone direct me to the stock\u00A0CFG for\u00A0landerCabinInternals so that I can manually create an offset version?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m welding a pod\u00A0with other parts and need to correct the location where the internal cabin \u0022part\u0022\u00A0gets attached to.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JPLRepo","CreatedById":114736,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-23T08:41:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can just add an\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOffset=X,y,z\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nto the internal definition you have above\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Fwiffo","CreatedById":148084,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-23T09:19:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/114736-jplrepo/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022114736\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/114736-jplrepo/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@JPLRepo\u003C/a\u003E SWEET, thanks!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-09-13T03:08:48Z\u0022 title=\u002209/13/2016 03:08  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 13, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Fwiffo\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JPLRepo","CreatedById":114736,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-23T09:23:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222596925\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022140343\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221463995162\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022148084\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Fwiffo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Fwiffo said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/114736-jplrepo/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022114736\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/114736-jplrepo/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@JPLRepo\u003C/a\u003E SWEET, thanks!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo elaborate a bit more, for others who might stumble onto this and I was on my phone before.\u003Cbr\u003E\nYes you can offset the Internal as follows:\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode prettyprint lang-html prettyprinted\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003EINTERNAL\n{\n\tname = landerCabinInternal\n\toffset = x,y,z\n}\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwhere the Offset is from the pivot point of the External Part model that it is attached to.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gamax19","CreatedById":157766,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-23T11:04:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nInteresting I never knew that you can do that thanks.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Fwiffo","CreatedById":148084,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-11T07:44:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan you do a rotation, too? \u00A0I tried adding \u0022rotate = 0, 0, 90\u0022 and \u0022rotation = 0, 0, 90\u0022 lines with no joy.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JPLRepo","CreatedById":114736,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-11T09:03:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222750640\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022140343\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221473579854\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022148084\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Fwiffo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Fwiffo said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan you do a rotation, too? \u00A0I tried adding \u0022rotate = 0, 0, 90\u0022 and \u0022rotation = 0, 0, 90\u0022 lines with no joy.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo I don\u0027t think it does.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Fwiffo","CreatedById":148084,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-13T03:45:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor anyone struggling to find the correct offset: On a craft I was recently tweaking I found I had to set the INTERNAL offset to: -X, -Z, -Y; where X, Y, Z were the MODEL position coordinates of my Lander Can Mk1.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}